{"word":"ἰαχή","slug":"ἰαχή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰαχή</b></el> <el>(ἰᾰχή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἰάχω'><el>ἰάχω</el></a>\n<p/><i>a cry, shout, wail, shriek</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: also <i>a joyous sound</i>, <el>ἰαχὰ ὑμεναίων</el> <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/> <hr/> <el><b>ἰαχή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <el>ἰαχή</el>\n"}]}